description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/kiss_transport.c
Lines: 710-726

kiss_transport_test_reset() acquires three mutexes in a specific order:

    k_mutex_lock(&ctx->tx_mutex, K_FOREVER);
    k_mutex_lock(&ctx->stats_mutex, K_FOREVER);
    k_mutex_lock(&ctx->params_mutex, K_FOREVER);
    ...
    k_mutex_unlock(&ctx->params_mutex);
    k_mutex_unlock(&ctx->stats_mutex);
    k_mutex_unlock(&ctx->tx_mutex);

While other functions only acquire one mutex at a time, this establishes a lock ordering. If any future code acquires these mutexes in a different order, it could deadlock.

Additionally, while the unlock order is reversed (correct), acquiring multiple mutexes for a test helper that's supposed to reset state is overly complex.

Fix: Consider using a single state_mutex for all mutable state, or document the required lock ordering, or simplify test_reset to not need multiple locks (e.g., by having an atomic "resetting" flag).
